          "username": "mayankg2703"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-02-01 05:48:03.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Michael.\n\nAs we discussed in OOM-328 tag should be removed or renamed due to parsing mechanism of pre-pull docker images.\n\nThanks,\nMayank Gupta",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "3462e4450c69332d6c97c059718ed4432f16bb44",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 137,
          "name": "Alexis de Talhouet",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "adetalhouet89@gmail.com",
          "username": "adetalhouet"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-02-01 13:10:46.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAh, so those changes and related are to satify the pre-pull script. Instead of having the image and the tag in a single line, let's standardize the way it should be, so the pre-pull script will know what to look for.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "a82a36352589ef23c5119ebdebd9af6a72f705b3",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2535,
          "name": "Mayank Gupta",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "mayank.gupta@amdocs.com",
          "username": "mayankg2703"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-02-01 13:57:10.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Alexis,\n\nRightly notice.\n\nI have explained parsing/scanning mechanism inside JIRA-328.\n\ncurrently:\nprepull script will take care two cases -\n1. if version is provided with image name itself.\n\nEg: readiness: oomk8s/readiness-check:1.0.0\n\n2. If  there is Version tag is in next line of image name.\n\naaiResourcesImage: nexus3.onap.org:10001/openecomp/aai-resources\naaiResourcesVersion: v1.1.0 \n\nIts mandatory to have Version as a sub string in next line of image name.\n\nshould we go for merge?\n\n\nThanks,\nMayank Gupta",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "231a9c0e45cc38a20c77b581d1e7b82da3ddbde3",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 497,
          "name": "Borislav Glozman",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "borislav.glozman@amdocs.com",
          "username": "BorislavG"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-02-01 14:22:15.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Hi Alexis,\n > \n > Rightly notice.\n > \n > I have explained parsing/scanning mechanism inside JIRA-328.\n > \n > currently:\n > prepull script will take care two cases -\n > 1. if version is provided with image name itself.\n > \n > Eg: readiness: oomk8s/readiness-check:1.0.0\n > \n > 2. If  there is Version tag is in next line of image name.\n > \n > aaiResourcesImage: nexus3.onap.org:10001/openecomp/aai-resources\n > aaiResourcesVersion: v1.1.0\n > \n > Its mandatory to have Version as a sub string in next line of image\n > name.\n > \n > should we go for merge?\n > \n > \n > Thanks,\n > Mayank Gupta\n\nThen maybe change repository -> configImageName\nand tag -> configImageVersion\nWhat do you think?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
