        "timestamp": "2018-02-02 20:52:10.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI'm not too familiar with the pre-pull script as I don't use it but I think getting the image tags from the integration manifest is a truer source of data than the values.yaml that we manually sync up at random.  Have we thought about getting the details from the manifest csv instead?\n\nIf we extract from all the values.yaml, with a pull policy of never and a mismatched image we will be alerted to any changes through the pod failing to find the \"actual\" image needed by the apps.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
